Un-rarefied without eukaryotes Plots

first Im going to read in the un rarefied data - this data has also had the ff1-3 anomaly smple removed and singletons removed

metadata<-read_q2metadata("metadata_grouped.txt") # must contain q2:types in second line
SVs<-read_qza("table-no-FF1-3.qza")$data
taxonomy<-read_qza("taxonomy.qza")$data %>% parse_taxonomy()

SVs <- as.data.frame(SVs)

remove any samples (controls/blanks) that you dont want to see in the plots

drops <- c("ctrl-1", "ctrl-2","ctrl-3", "mock-4", "mock-12")
SVs <- SVs[ , !(names(SVs) %in% drops)]
metadata<- metadata %>% 
  filter(`Keep`=="Yes") # to drop all banks used Keep2

for some reason after parse taxonomy d__ remain in the kingdom column, so Ive removed it manually

taxonomy$Kingdom <- gsub("d__", "",taxonomy$Kingdom)

Species Plots

Im now removing Eukaryota and plotting the data

taxasums<-summarize_taxa(SVs, taxonomy)$Species

taxsums_noEuk<- taxasums[!grepl("Eukaryota.*", row.names(taxasums)),]

taxa_heatmap(taxsums_noEuk, metadata, "Preservative")

taxa_barplot(taxsums_noEuk, metadata, "Preservative")

Genus Plots

and without Eukaryota by genus

taxasumsgenus<-summarize_taxa(SVs, taxonomy)$Genus

taxsumsgenus_noEuk<- taxasumsgenus[!grepl("Eukaryota.*", row.names(taxasumsgenus)),]

taxa_heatmap(taxsumsgenus_noEuk, metadata, "Preservative")

taxa_barplot(taxsumsgenus_noEuk, metadata, "Preservative")

Rarefied-36800 without Eukaryota

now Im having a look at the rarefied to 36800 data without Eukaryota

metadata<-read_q2metadata("metadata_grouped.txt") # must contain q2:types in second line
SVs<-read_qza("rarefied_table-no-FF1-3.qza")$data
taxonomy<-read_qza("taxonomy.qza")$data %>% parse_taxonomy()

SVs <- as.data.frame(SVs)

taxonomy$Kingdom <- gsub("d__", "",taxonomy$Kingdom)

Species Plots

taxasums<-summarize_taxa(SVs, taxonomy)$Species

# removing Eukaryota from taxasums
taxsums_noEuk<- taxasums[!grepl("Eukaryota.*", row.names(taxasums)),]

taxa_heatmap(taxsums_noEuk, metadata, "Preservative")

ggsave("heatmap_rarefied36800_species_noEuk_no-FF1-3.pdf", height=4, width=8, device="pdf") # save a PDF 4 inches by 8 inches

taxa_barplot(taxsums_noEuk, metadata, "Preservative")

ggsave("barplot_rarefied36800_species_noEuk_no-FF1-3.pdf", height=4, width=8, device="pdf") # save a PDF 4 inches by 8 inches

Genus Plots

taxasumsgenus<-summarize_taxa(SVs, taxonomy)$Genus

# removing Eukaryota from taxasums
taxsumsgenus_noEuk<- taxasumsgenus[!grepl("Eukaryota.*", row.names(taxasumsgenus)),]

taxa_heatmap(taxsumsgenus_noEuk, metadata, "Preservative")

ggsave("heatmap_rarefied36800_genus_noEuk_no-FF1-3.pdf", height=4, width=8, device="pdf") # save a PDF 4 inches by 8 inches

taxa_barplot(taxsumsgenus_noEuk, metadata, "Preservative")

ggsave("barplot_rarefied36800_genus_noEuk_no-FF1-3.pdf", height=4, width=8, device="pdf") # save a PDF 4 inches by 8 inches
